node.text:
Would you dare to walk on this Via Ferrata? 😳 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tripfever.net (link in my bio: @tripfever)

The new Ferrata Delle Aquile, on the top of Paganella, is a highly emotional and spectacular via ferrata that gives you unforgettable emotions; the sight embraces whole Trentino, but keeping fixed on the track too.

Recommendation:
Avoid the queue: purchase online your ticket and go directly to turnstile. Choose the stage and pay with your credit card. You will receive by email your ticket (you can print the ticket or save it in your smartphone), scan it on the orange scanner on the turnstile located at the gates of the lift.

📽 @borievkyphotogallery
📍Trentino, Italy

node.text:
An orca during sunset in Alaska via @marysmark 🐋 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tripfever.net (link in my bio: @tripfever)

Swipe to see all the photos and tag a @nature lover!

The killer whale or orca (Orcinus orca) is a toothed whale belonging to the oceanic dolphin family, of which it is the largest member. It is recognizable by its black-and-white patterned body. A cosmopolitan species, killer whales are found in all oceans and most seas in a variety of marine environments, from Arctic and Antarctic regions to tropical seas; they are absent only from the Baltic and Black seas, and some areas of the Arctic Ocean.

📸 @marysmark
📍 Alaska

node.text:
Sunsets in Santorini 🌅 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @tripfever

Tag a friend who you’d escape to Greece with!

Loved for its one of a kind architecture and beach views, this Greek town will take your breath away. If you’re visiting Santorini this summer, don’t forget to hike to the town’s volcano and unwind at a winery afterwards ☀️🍷

📷 @cbezerraphotos & @_letstravel_
📍 Santorini, Greece
